<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 32 (July 9th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><B>Maridian Education (R)</B></li><ul><li>Enemies can now dispel out of the displacement portion of this ability.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 31 (June 17th, 2014)</h4><p>Updated auto attack animations.</p><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Reprimand (Q)</li><ul><li>The displayed range of this ability has been updated to 170, from previous value of 190.</li></ul><li>Force Slam (W)</li><ul><li>The displayed range of this ability has been updated to 450, from previous value of 500.</li><li>The Power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.45, down from 0.6.</li></ul><li>Maridian Education (R)</li><ul><li>The displayed range of this ability has been updated to 275, from previous value of 300.</li><li>The Power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.9,d own from 1.1.</li><li>The base damage for the secondary damage if the target is hit into a wall or structure has been reduced to 175/300/425, down from 200/375/550.</li><li>The Power ratio for the secondary damage of this ability has been reduced to 0.7, down from 1.1</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 13 (October 13, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Force Wave (W)</B></li><ul><li>The cast range of this ability has been increased to 500, up from 450.</li></ul><li><B>Unyielding Progress (E)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been increased to 240/330/420/510/600, up from 210/300/390/480/570.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 11 (August 29, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Hypersonic Punch (R)</B></li><ul><li>This ability will now knock aside any enemy Shaper that gets hit by the primary target as it is knocked back.</li><li>The primary target hitbox has been increased by 75%.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 8 (August 09, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Demi (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The percentage health damage on this ability has increased to 3/6/9/12/15%, up from 2.5/5/7.5/10/12.5%.</li></ul><li><B>Unyielding Progress (E)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability for a full duration spin has been increased to 210/300/390/480/570, up from 180/270/360/450/540.</li><li>The power ratio for a full duration spin has been increased to 1.8, up from 1.5.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 7 (August 02, 2013)</h4><ul><li>Basic attack range increased to 130, up from 95.</li><li><B>Reprimand (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been increased to 75/100/125/150/175, up from 75/95/115/135/155. The cooldown of this ability has been decreased to 9/8/7/6/5, down from 10/9/8/7/6.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 5 (July 18, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Unyielding Progress (E)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been increased to 180/270/360/450/540, up from 180/255/330/405/480.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 4 (July 14, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Unyielding Progress (E)</B></li><ul><li>Added text to the level up tooltip on this ability to correctly display the amount of slowing effect reduced by this ability at each rank.</li></ul></ul>